description.description_en: Glaucescent perennial herbs with globose tubers; stems tufted, slender, glabrous, decumbent, erect above, 10-30 cm long.Leaves few, the radical ones long-petioled, 2- to 3-ternate; leaflets 2- to 3-parted or -cleft, segmants thin, oblanceolate to obovate, 1-2 cm long, 3-7 mm wide; cauline leaves usually 2, short-petioled, 2-ternate.Flowers rose to blue-purple, few, in racemes; bracts rhombic-ovate, entire, subacute.Capsules linear, ca. 2 cm long, slightly torulose; seeds dark brown, minutely mammillate.
